
-Apple has gradually developed separate OS's for its varioius technologies: Ipad, watch, appleTV, iphone, mac 
-the splintering of technology has made developing for all Apple systems very difficult 
-SwiftUI is an abstraction layer that sits on top of previous development tools and allows development of UIs that work on all platforms 
-SwiftUI only works for the most recent versions of these technologies: macOS Catalina, iOS 13, tvOS 13, watchOS 6, iPadOS 

-XCode11 includes SDKs for all 5 of the platforms listed, and compilers for C, C++, objective-C, and Swift 
-XCode uses the LLVM compiler, which can compile code written in C, C++, objective-C, and Swift 






